    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Leave Heating Oil To the Private Sector</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>B Meredith Burke letter says solution to heating crisis is to live within our ecological means, and also to develop efficient technology</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What Representative Joseph Kennedy 2d's calls ''the best long-term approach to a heating oil crisis'' (Op-Ed, Dec. 7) should encompass two elements, neither of which he considers. One is a long-term population policy to insure that we live within our ecological means. The other is a strengthened program to develop and encourage efficient technology for utilizing renewable energy sources.</p>
        <p>B. MEREDITH  BURKE</p>
        <p>Palo Alto, Calif., Dec. 9, 1996</p>
        <p>The writer is a visiting scholar at the Hoover Institution.</p>
      </block>
